<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/238045-who-would-you-say-suffers-more-from">Who would you say suffers more from self-denial? Dido or Aeneid? And why?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_238045'><a id="like_count_community_question_238045" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/238045?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">3 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F12914.The_Aeneid">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/238045-who-would-you-say-suffers-more-from">6 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/238045-who-would-you-say-suffers-more-from">See all 5 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/54276691-heather-purri"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1458952675i/54276691._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/54276691-heather-purri">Heather Purri</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Dido suffers from self-denial; Aeneas suffers, period. Dido&apos;s husband, Sychaeus, had died and he was her one true love. Dido incorrectly assumes that <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Dido suffers from self-denial; Aeneas suffers, period. Dido's husband, Sychaeus, had died and he was her one true love. Dido incorrectly assumes that Juno/Hera delaying Aeneas's departure will give him time to fall in love with her. When he leaves, he tells her the truth-that he never loved her-rather than a beautiful and comforting lie. Aeneas suffers because his wife, Creusa, literally just died in the Trojan War and Aeneas is a single father now. In the Underworld, it breaks Aeneas's heart to see that Dido died, but she will not hear his apologies and flaunts her reunion with Sychaeus. But, someday, Aeneas will reunite with Creusa.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

<div class='flagAnswer'>
<a class="right flag" rel="nofollow" id="flag_link845151" title="Flag this answer as inappropriate." href="/flagged/new?resource_id=845151&amp;resource_type=CommunityAnswer&amp;return_url=%2Fquestions%2F238045-who-would-you-say-suffers-more-from%2Fanswers%2F845151-dido-suffers-from">flag</a>
</div>
<ul class='communityQAFooter answerFooter'>
</ul>

</div>
